Package org.generator.services

Class ExcelService

java.lang.Object
org.generator.services.ExcelService
@Service public class ExcelService extends Object
Service class responsible for reading and processing data from Excel files. The readStudentsFromExcel() method handles the extraction of student and group information, ensuring uniqueness and associating group leaders. The processed data is then saved using the GroupService.

  • Method Details

    • readStudentsFromExcel

      public void readStudentsFromExcel()
      Reads student and group data from an Excel file specified by studentsExcelPath. Extracts student names and group codes, creating unique StudentDTO and studentsExcelPath objects. Associates students with their groups and identifies group leaders. Saves all unique groups (and associated students) using GroupService.save(GroupDTO). This method takes no parameters and returns no value.

    • readProfessorsFromExcel

      public void readProfessorsFromExcel()
      Reads professor and assistant data from an Excel file specified by professorsExcelPath. Extracts professor full names, associated courses, and assistant names from each row. Creates Professor entities for both professors and their assistants, assigning the correct rank ("Profesor" or "Asistent"). Saves all created Professor entities using ProfessorService.save(Professor). It handles potential IOException during file reading and logs any errors encountered.
